      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Ah, yes, the NeuroZest Phase II trials were a resounding success, with participants exhibiting a 90% improvement in cognitive function after just six weeks of treatment. Our advanced predictive modeling suggested a 98% efficacy rate, and our team made a groundbreaking adjustment to the dosing schedule that significantly boosted results. I presented these findings to the FDA themselves last quarter, and they've been eagerly awaiting our latest batch of test results, which will confirm the results. We're essentially a done deal, and I'll have the full report to share with the board in just an hour.\"",
